				Let me see if I have this correct.  I get a title for trying to upgrade certain aspects of my character.  Didn't ask for it, don't want it, but have no choice in it.<BR>
If it causes some type of prob, other people or I can petition a GM and it may be turned off or on based on some policy that I have no control of.  <BR>
I've got two characters that have only one name, one  character that has two. (Two mules that I don't count)  I chose those names, they fit my characters and the way I play them.  Notice I said I chose them.  Did not and do not want titles.  But aparently Verant in its infinite wisdom will assign them to me.  I do not know why, possibly some small pecentage of players wish to add titles to feed their egos?  You did some good when you added the possibility of customizing faces, that was a good decision. Adding titles that no one that I have talked to wants, probably a bad decision.  Adding a title to my paladin would be a total reversal of the philosophy in which I try to play him.  His motto:<BR>
<BR>
Just a poor paladin traveling through Norrath.<BR>
<BR>
I truly believe you forget who does pay to play the game.  Did you do some survey I missed to find out if anyone really wants these titles?  Can't implement a one time choice for the player to accept or decline the title? You can't offer a player the option, from the message, to turn it off themselves cause those people working on something else.  Ahhh here's an idea, put it on the list to be fixed, just don't have to have it dome tomorrow. I would be willing to wait for a toggle on it.  I know there would be a problems with a one time decision, people would be petitioning to change that decision all the time, but I know I could live with it.  You may think something as simple as this title business is of no real importance, but I for one will say, leave my name alone.
